parameters:
According to multiple sources, in the early Edo period,
there were young female spirit mediums who traveled from
place to place, subduing harmful mononoke and strange
apparitions.

The documents concerning her are varied, and there is
evidence confirming her existence in the records of feudal
lords. It's clear that she was not merely a figure of
folklore or fairy tales, yet her true nature remains
terribly vague.

It is said that she was a young and beautiful shrine maiden
with white hair, and a skilled swordsman capable of calming
a mysterious bird that disturbed the capital with a single
stroke.

It is said that she loved children enough to exorcise
spirits that cursed infants and to care for sick children,
and for some reason, she used a small shrine as her base of
operations and never strayed far from it.

It is said that while she saved many people, her name has
not been passed down, and at some point, she suddenly
vanished without a trace of her journey.

All of these aspects draw my interest inexorably. Who was
she? I intend to continue my research. Author: Eijiro Osako
